sentences: Zdenka Ticharich (Zdenka von Ticharich)  (26 September 1900 – 15 February 1979) was a Hungarian pianist, music educator and composer.

She studied with István Tomka at the National School of Music, and then with Ferruccio Busoni and Emil Sauer at the Berlin University of the Arts, and composition with Franz Schreker from 1923 to 1925.
From 1947-1969 Ticharich taught piano at the Budapest Academy of Music.
Capriccio by Berthold Goldschmidt (1903–1996) was composed for Ticharich in 1927.
